Hello,

Use ?mapply to cycle through all values of a and b.
Note that the output matrices are transposed, the random vectors are the 
rows.


library(Surrogate)

a <- c(0.1, 0.2)
b <- c(0.2, 0.8)
mapply(\(a, b, s, n, m) RandVec(a, b, s, n, m),
        MoreArgs = list(s = 1, n = 2, m = 5), a, b)
