The R antibugging practice here is to not use the return function. The expression on the last line of the function is automatically the return value of the function. Some people use return within conditionals in the function, but when I have conditional execution flow I prefer to simply assign alternate return values to a local variable along different execution paths and require all execution paths to reach the end of the function where that variable name is alone on the last line.

